content.description: SDS. climb easier moves to a crimpy and intense overhanging arete/roof. good body positioning makes some of the harder moves easier. there is a hard crux at the end on bad slopes with technical heel hooks that can demolish any good effort if not done correctly. long.
content.location: backside of the boulder opposite from hammer of hate.

content.description: Starts on the same jug as the imp, goes up and left using small flat ledges
content.location: Left of the imp.  See the imp for a photo of the boulder

content.description: Start sitting with a left crimping on the arete, right on the face. Make a big move to jugs up high, topout.
content.location: On the same boulder as Hammer of Hate, on the opposite side facing away from the wash. Climbs a small prow.

content.description: Clean, fun line left of The Imp. Start low on a left hand undercling and sweet right hand pinch just below the jug for The Imp. Situate your feet on the seem that runs across the kicker (obviously the random rocks at the bottom are off), make a good move out left to a good hold, then bump the right hand onto a sweet side pull with a thumb catch. From here bring the right foot up and fire left hand to a long powerful throw to a nice lip. Squeeze and pray the right foot sticks. Control the barn door, then top out to sweet sweet jugs.
content.location: Starts just below The Imp.

content.description: Start on sloping edges, climb slippery crimps to easy topout. Depending on the season and rainfall, the landing of this climb is occasionally a stagnant pool. Avoid splashing down into the pools, and rumors of dog eating swamp monsters should not be ignored.
content.location: About 6 feet left of Action Arete on south face of Boxcar Boulder

content.description:
Start on two sloping ledges, contort your feet under somewhere (maybe not as hard if you aren't 6+ feet), then move up to good holds, then topout. Lowball but fun. 

  You can start a little lower with your left hand on the arete and right hand in a sharp crimp. A little harder, but not as good.
content.location: On west end of boulder below Sleepy Hollow.

content.description:
start on a slopey, blocky undercling. pulling off the ground takes some muscle. throw a HUGE move to a good hold, toe hook next to your left hand on the starting undercling, fire to a left hand side-pull, and figure out the rest.  

  a stout project. although it goes with out saying, the name is tentative and in place for practical reference.
content.protection: pads + spotter off of the large dead tree
content.location: in the roof/cave above the hammer area. an obvious black roof with very few features.

content.description: Good holds on bullet granite go right up the center this beautiful Boulder. There is a small shelf of rock at the base making it so you’re never really over your pads. A fall off this thing will be memorable.
content.location: Massive triangular Boulder that’s top out is visible from the approach. Just head down the wash a ways from the main cluster and this will be up on your left. This is just behind The Imp and Tigger Style.

content.description: Start sitting on boulder, hands on big sloping rails. Move up to good sidepull, then gun for the top. To avoid a funky tiered landing, just move a little left to topout on Action Arete.
content.location: On east face of Boxcar Boulder

content.description:
Climb the black water streak on the obvious tall face in the hammer of hate area. there is a lower start beginning on two horrendously polished crimps and a bad foot that is much harder.  

  a fall from the top of this would result in certain injury. the crux is at the top, and involved a right hand lock off of a small, incut pinch off of a high left toe. committing, but extremely fun! the boulder that it is on is beautiful!
begin on sloping edges, and lunge for the triangle shaped crimp.   a sit start adds a few hard moves and feels to be in the v7-9 range
content.location: middle of the face opposite the wu tang sword on the boxcar boulder

content.description: sit start to moonboard. adds a few more moves on bad, sloping, polished crimps

Sit start with a right hand crimp and left on a jug.  Crimps and slopers out right and left hand stays on the slopey far side of the boulder to top-out.  Dont go to the right of the seam or its a different problem and much easier
content.location:
Leftmost climb on the vineyard Boulder.   

  The Vineyard Boulder is on the left side of the stream, further down stream from it cliff and the Hammer of hate area

content.description: start on two ball like slopers that are polished like marble and climb the obvious face
content.location: when facing no man's land (v3), it is the boulder up the wash to the left of the no man's land boulder

content.description:
Sit start from block...moving a little right, then pulling up into the face. Climb fractured cracks to easy topout. 

boulderingtucson.com/molino…
content.location: On the (north?) face of the boulder facing away from the creek bed.

content.description:
Start on lower left side of boulder on low ledge. Move up and right to rounded holds, then up and right to lip.  

  Font Variation - from starting holds, move straight up to rounded bulge, topout. v0+
content.location: On the black, sooty-looking boulder just below Sleepy Hollow cave.

content.description:
Climb up to the obvious and suspect flake (don't pull too hard), continue strait up. Topout as far to the right as you can, it's much safer that way. 

  TREAD LIGHTLY!
content.location: Just to the right of No Man's Land.

content.description: Start sitting on crimp jugs and a good little foot edge. slap with your left hand up two alright slopers then fire a long move out left to a sharp crimp then top out.
content.location: hike down the canyon away from the parking until the canyon forks left. Passing It cliff, follow the canyon left for a few mins. you will pass a cool looking cube boulder on your left. The Sorcerers Stone be on your right within 20 yards or so.

content.description: The route is in between two rocks, start further in on the left sitting on crimps and the route moves upwards and right
content.location: Behind the vineyard bouder 15 feet and to the left

content.description: Mantle the first small boulder, undercling on the roof, then use sidepulls, laybacks, and gastons to move up and right. No matter how you do it you have to trust a sloping left foot. Scary.
content.protection: Pads and a spot, popping off one of the layback moves would be brutal.
content.location: On the left side of the Boxcar Boulder facing the wash. Starts on the boulder that is actually holding supporting the Boxcar.

content.description: Start on the big jug in the middle of the wall, half dyno move to a diagonal/sideways hold up a few feet and to the right a little. then a move or two and top out
content.location: Behind the vineyard boulder maybe 20 or 30 feet and to the left a little.  This Route goes to the right, Witches and Warlock starts the same but goes left

content.description: Start on low ledge, move up to an incut flake, then right to a sidepull between the boulders, then up to a couple good holds, then the lip. Topout is a little tricky trying not to dab on the boulder behind you.
content.location: Just below Sleepy Hollow, this climb starts near the junction of the two boulders.

content.description: good variety of movement. SDS. technical moves + power. start left hand on a jug sidepull and a bad right hand slopey crimp and make two powerful beginning moves into easier ones before a hard and technical top out.
content.location: straight down the canyon past the obvious black roof, there is a freestanding boulder with one line on the overhanging portion of it. this is the hammer of hate. it is lowball,  but climbs well. on the left before the It Cliff when heading down the canyon from the molino basin parking lot.

content.description: Start matched on the low jug and go up the hanging dihedral.
content.location: On the Battle Tackle boulder, the corner(N) adjacent to Battle Tackle.

content.description: Fun overhanging arete. A low and powerful start helps you gain a cool jugs to an easy topout. Look out for bees!
content.location: Located on the downstream side of a dark gray boulder a 100 feet past the Boxcar Boulder.

content.description: Start in a flare in a seam, with a left hand finger lock, right hand gaston. Paste your feet on, make a long move to the slopey ledge. Match, move up to good crimp, then up to easy but dirty topout. Look out for a small cactus growing on one of the topout ledges.
content.location: Just below Sleepy Hollow cave, look for obvious thin seam in the black streak.

content.description: Same Start as Merlins Merlot but as you move up it heads right up the more juggy middle of the boulder
content.location: Middle route on the vineyard boulder   The Vineyard Boulder is on the left side of the stream, further down stream from it cliff and the Hammer of hate area

content.description: Sit start on the right of the vineyard boulder and climb up the jugs
content.location: Right side of the vineyard boulder   The Vineyard Boulder is on the left side of the stream, further down stream from it cliff and the Hammer of hate area

content.description: Start matched on a good incut on the overhang, and climb an overhanging arete to a difficult finish over a bad landing (make sure to place pads well). on the left as you head down the canyon. in the same area as hammer of hate. Original method eliminated the supporting boulder for feet. Do what makes you happy!
Start standing on sloping ledges. Climb up through more slopey ledges to a slightly tricky topout.
content.location: On the Boxcar Boulder (big rectangular boulder on right side of stream as you walk down), the southeast arete on the boulder.

content.description: Start sitting with a sloping leftward facing rail and a right hand crimp. Put your toe high up and pull off the ground. A single hard move to a jug puts you at the beginning of the stand.

Start left hand on a 2 pad flat jug,  right hamd on a crimp. Find a good toe, rock up and right to a small sidepull, then balance up and left to another sidepull. Move up to a good hold, then an easy topout.
content.location: Right next to Headless Horseman, on the next boulder. Below Sleepy Hollow.

content.description: This is a nice low elevation bouldering area in a beautiful little canyon. There are a handful of really nice boulders to be climbed on, with some great moderate problems and some really good harder ones. The rock is a bit water polished, but has really nice features and is mostly super solid. The landings of some of the climbs are occasionally under standing water.
